   The Division of the State Architect - DSA

   The Division of the State Architect (DSA) acts as California's policy
   leader for building design and construction, and provides design and
   construction oversight for K-12 schools and community colleges. DSA has
   offices in Los Angeles, Oakland, Sacramento, and San Diego.

   DSA also develops and maintains the accessibility standards and codes
   utilized in public and private buildings throughout California. See
   DSA's "Universal Design" pages for more information.

   DSA incorporates the offices of the independent State Historical
   Building Safety Board, caretaker of California's State Historical
   Building Code.


